Ayanami, Asuka, are you in position yet?

104
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:37,663
Not yet.

105
00:06:37,664 --> 00:06:38,397
You know there's no way
we could move that fast!
Not yet.

106
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,238
You know there's no way
we could move that fast!

107
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:48,747
Power Source

108
00:06:57,851 --> 00:06:59,141
Not there yet?

109
00:07:03,623 --> 00:07:05,353
Il go ahead and stop it on my own.

110
00:07:08,228 --> 00:07:09,695
It disappeared!

111
00:07:09,696 --> 00:07:10,496
What?!

112
00:07:10,497 --> 00:07:11,196
Pattern blue! Angel confirmed!
Directly beneath Unit 01!
What?!

113
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:12,977
Pattern blue! Angel confirmed!
Directly beneath Unit 01!

114
00:07:13,767 --> 00:07:15,057
A shadow?!

115
00:07:17,237 --> 00:07:19,257
What is this?! It's weird!

116
00:07:22,075 --> 00:07:23,715
Shinji, get out of there! Shin;ji?!

117
00:07:24,477 --> 00:07:25,077
Ikari?

118
00:07:25,078 --> 00:07:25,978
You idiot, what are you doing?!
Ikari?

119
00:07:25,979 --> 00:07:26,709
You idiot, what are you doing?!

120
00:07:29,215 --> 00:07:32,017
Miss Misato, what's going on?!

121
00:07:32,018 --> 00:07:35,054
Miss Misato? Asuka! Ayanami!
Where's the backup?

122
00:07:35,055 --> 00:07:36,555
Miss Misato?! Can you hear me?! Miss Misato!

123
00:07:36,556 --> 00:07:38,490
Eject the plug! Send the signal!
Miss Misato?! Can you hear me?! Miss Misato!

124
00:07:38,491 --> 00:07:40,326
It's not working! No response!

125
00:07:40,327 --> 00:07:42,257
Miss Misato! Miss Misato!

126
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:45,698
Shinji!

127
00:07:45,699 --> 00:07:47,719
Asuka! Rei! Rescue Unit 01! Hurry!

128
00:07:48,535 --> 00:07:51,195
That idiot. What's the point of doing well
only on practice exams?!

129
00:07:54,441 --> 00:07:55,341
It disappeared again.

130
00:07:55,342 --> 00:07:56,575
Asuka, be careful.

131
00:07:56,576 --> 00:07:57,866
A shadow?

132
00:08:06,086 --> 00:08:07,346
No!

133
00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:21,433
The city!

134
00:08:21,434 --> 00:08:23,214
Asuka, Rei, pull back.

135
00:08:24,004 --> 00:08:24,269
Bu...

136
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:25,637
Wait!
Bu...

137
00:08:25,638 --> 00:08:27,248
Unit 01 and Ikari are still in there.

138
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:31,365
This is an order. Retreat.

139
00:08:41,821 --> 00:08:44,041
This must be tough for Major Katsuragi.

140
00:08:44,924 --> 00:08:47,092
They reeled the umbilical cable back in,

141
00:08:47,093 --> 00:08:48,613
but the other end was missing.

142
00:08:49,429 --> 00:08:50,629
Then...

143
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:53,365
There's not much energy
in the internal batteries.

144
00:08:53,366 --> 00:08:55,467
But if Shinji doesn't just
flail around with the Eva,

145
00:08:55,468 --> 00:08:57,669
and can hang in there in life support mode,

146
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:59,400
then he can survive for sixteen hours.

147
00:09:02,709 --> 00:09:04,410
Second Tank Platoon deployed.

148
00:09:04,411 --> 00:09:06,211
Roger. Hold your current positions and stand by.

149
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:08,680
Sub laser circuit has been opened.
Transmitting data now.

150
00:09:08,681 --> 00:09:10,411
Confirmed. New line transmitting data.

151
00:09:11,184 --> 00:09:13,174
The UN forces have completely surrounded it.

152
00:09:13,987 --> 00:09:14,920
What about the shadow?

153
00:09:14,921 --> 00:09:16,288
It hasn't moved.

154
00:09:16,289 --> 00:09:19,792
It stopped spreading once it reached
a diameter of just over 600 meters.

155
00:09:19,793 --> 00:09:22,861
But are the ground troops going to be any use?

156
00:09:22,862 --> 00:09:26,031
They think they're applying pressure on us.

157
00:09:26,032 --> 00:09:27,599
Good grief!

158
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,668
Taking matters into his own hands,
ignoring the plan.

159
00:09:29,669 --> 00:09:32,271
Honestly, talk about getting what he deserved.

160
00:09:32,272 --> 00:09:35,140
Just because he got a little better score
on yesterday's tests,

161
00:09:35,141 --> 00:09:36,781
he was going to show me how it's done?!

162
00:09:37,877 --> 00:09:39,337
What a big-headed idiot!

163
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:44,967
What? Is my bad-mouthing of Shinji
that much of a problem for you?!

164
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:50,522
Do you pilot Eva just for the praise of others?

165
00:09:50,523 --> 00:09:54,593
No! Not of others! I do it because
I want to be able to praise myself!

166
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,054
Cut it out, you two!

167
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:59,350
That's right, he went out on his own.

168
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,480
So I'll just have to scold him
when he comes back.

169
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:26,813
I never thought sleeping
could be this exhausting.

170
00:10:33,032 --> 00:10:35,200
Still blank.

171
00:10:35,201 --> 00:10:38,891
No radar or sonar reflections at all.
This space must be too big.

172
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:43,834
It's been twelve hours since
I switched to life-support mode.

173
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:49,290
So my life will end in another four or five hours.

174
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:52,618
I'm hungry.

175
00:10:52,619 --> 00:10:55,521
So, that shadow is actually the Angel's body?

176
00:10:55,522 --> 00:10:58,457
Correct. It's six hundred eighty
meters in diameter

177
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:00,098
with a thickness of three nanometers.

178
00:11:01,361 --> 00:11:05,230
The ultra-thin space is supported by
an inwardly-directed AT Field.

179
00:11:05,231 --> 00:11:08,233
The inside is an imaginary space,
called a Sea of Dirac.

180
00:11:08,234 --> 00:11:11,069
I think it's probably connected
to another universe.

181
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:12,704
What about the sphere?

182
00:11:12,705 --> 00:11:14,985
It disappears when the imaginary circuit
of the body closes.

183
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:18,092
The object in the sky is the real shadow.

184
00:11:18,978 --> 00:11:21,997
So the black shadow that swallowed
Unit 01 is the target.

185
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,216
Then there's no way that we can fight it.

186
00:11:32,358 --> 00:11:34,092
The water is getting cloudy!

187
00:11:34,093 --> 00:11:35,823
The purification system is giving out.

188
00:11:37,497 --> 00:11:39,031
It stinks in here!

189
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:41,099
Blood! It smells of blood!

190
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,168
No! I don't want to be here!

191
00:11:43,169 --> 00:11:45,571
Why can't l open the lock?

192
00:11:45,572 --> 00:11:47,940
Open up! Let me out!

193
00:11:47,941 --> 00:11:49,641
Miss Misato, what's going on?!

194
00:11:49,642 --> 00:11:52,162
Miss Misato! Asuka! Ayanami!

195
00:11:53,112 --> 00:11:54,401
Miss Ritsuko!

196
00:11:55,148 --> 00:11:56,438
Father...

197
00:12:00,286 --> 00:12:02,955
Please, someone help me.

198
00:12:02,956 --> 00:12:04,890
A forced Eva salvage?

199
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:07,231
It's the only possibility that might work.

200
00:12:08,361 --> 00:12:13,332
We would drop all 992 existing
N2 mines into its center,

201
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:17,135
while simultaneously activating the
AT Fields of the remaining Evas,

202
00:12:17,136 --> 00:12:20,505
disrupting the Angel's imaginary circuit
for one millisecond.

203
00:12:20,506 --> 00:12:23,742
In that instant, we'll concentrate
all the explosive energy,

204
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:26,511
and destroy the Angel along
with the Sea of Dirac that forms it.

205
00:12:26,512 --> 00:12:30,315
But with that, the body of the Eva...
There's no telling what would happen to Shiniji.

206
00:12:30,316 --> 00:12:32,050
That can't be called a rescue operation!

207
00:12:32,051 --> 00:12:35,487
This operation's top priority is
to recover Unit 01 itself.

208
00:12:35,488 --> 00:12:37,889
Heavy damage to the body is irrelevant.

209
00:12:37,890 --> 00:12:39,224
Now wait a second!

210
00:12:39,225 --> 00:12:41,505
In this case, the pilot's life is not our concern.

211
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:51,597
If Shinji's lost, it's your fault. Don't forget that!

212
00:12:53,172 --> 00:12:56,652
Why are you and Commander lkari
so worried about Unit 01?

213
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:00,512
What in the hell is an Eva?

214
00:13:00,513 --> 00:13:02,748
I've given you all the information.

215
00:13:02,749 --> 00:13:04,039
You're lying!

216
00:13:06,819 --> 00:13:08,868
Misato, trust me.

217
00:13:12,492 --> 00:13:15,592
I'm taking command of this entire operation.

218
00:13:20,233 --> 00:13:21,900
We'll be sending some flights to
Kansai International Airport as well.

219
00:13:21,901 --> 00:13:24,536
Contact Air Traffic Control and the
JADF's Air Transport divisions.

220
00:13:24,537 --> 00:13:25,737
Roger.

221
00:13:25,738 --> 00:13:30,142
The Second Impact, the
Instrumentality Project, Adam...

222
00:13:30,143 --> 00:13:32,013
There are still secrets that I'm in the dark about.

223
00:13:39,185 --> 00:13:40,525
Who's there?

224
00:13:45,425 --> 00:13:46,795
Who's there?

225
00:13:48,161 --> 00:13:49,828
Shinji Ikari.

226
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:51,430
That's me.

227
00:13:51,431 --> 00:13:55,211
I am you. People have another
self within themselves.

228
00:13:56,269 --> 00:13:58,549
The self is always composed of two people.

229
00:13:59,405 --> 00:14:00,405
Two people?

230
00:14:00,406 --> 00:14:04,142
The self which is actually seen,
and the self observing that.

231
00:14:04,143 --> 00:14:07,145
There are many entities called Shinji lkari.

232
00:14:07,146 --> 00:14:10,549
The other Shiniji Ikari that exists in your mind.

233
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:13,485
The Shiniji Ikari in Misato Katsuragi's mind,

234
00:14:13,486 --> 00:14:15,253
the Shinji in Asuka Sohryu,

235
00:14:15,254 --> 00:14:16,755
the Shinji in Rei Ayanami,

236
00:14:16,756 --> 00:14:18,724
and the Shinji in Gendo lkari.

237
00:14:18,725 --> 00:14:20,992
All are different Shinji lkaris,

238
00:14:20,993 --> 00:14:23,295
but each of them is a true Shinji lkari.

239
00:14:23,296 --> 00:14:26,765
You are afraid of those Shiniji lkaris
in other people's minds.

240
00:14:26,766 --> 00:14:29,101
I'm afraid of other people hating me.

241
00:14:29,102 --> 00:14:31,031
You're afraid of being hurt.

242
00:14:32,739 --> 00:14:34,306
Who is at fault?

243
00:14:34,307 --> 00:14:36,074
Father is the one who is at fault.

244
00:14:36,075 --> 00:14:38,043
The father who deserted me.

245
00:14:38,044 --> 00:14:39,277
It's my fault.

246
00:14:39,278 --> 00:14:42,147
There you go, always immediately thinking
that it's your fault!

247
00:14:42,148 --> 00:14:43,928
That's why I say you're self-deprecating!

248
00:14:44,384 --> 00:14:46,618
I can't do anything.

249
00:14:46,619 --> 00:14:48,519
You just believe that you can't do anything.

250
00:14:50,223 --> 00:14:52,032
Don't you have faith in your father?

251
00:14:52,825 --> 00:14:55,961
I think I hate him, but now I'm not sure.

252
00:14:55,962 --> 00:14:58,363
